I don't want to hear back from aunt Louise
about any misbehavior, Roy.

117
00:05:58,419 --> 00:06:00,257
- No, sir.
- He'll be fine, Edward.

118
00:06:00,257 --> 00:06:02,072
Aunt was good 
enough to find you a job.

119
00:06:02,072 --> 00:06:04,045
- You turn your wages over to her.
- Yes, sir.

120
00:06:04,045 --> 00:06:06,496
- And wear the garments.
- Yes, always.

121
00:06:06,496 --> 00:06:09,105
- Or what?
- Hellfire and brimstone, sir, gnashing of teeth.

122
00:06:09,105 --> 00:06:11,356
He's a good boy, I can tell.

123
00:06:11,356 --> 00:06:13,470
You heard about the girl, in Provo?

124
00:06:13,470 --> 00:06:15,884
Yes. That's why he's here.

125
00:06:15,884 --> 00:06:18,290
For a clean slate. To reform.

126
00:06:18,290 --> 00:06:20,391
I'll wear my garmies.
I'll have only clean thoughts.

127
00:06:20,391 --> 00:06:21,859
And?

128
00:06:25,446 --> 00:06:29,987
Never ever disrepect the Lord.

129
00:06:31,155 --> 00:06:32,552
Roy?

130
00:06:32,552 --> 00:06:34,821
- Are you listening to me?
- Yes, sir.

131
00:06:34,821 --> 00:06:38,102
Do not disrespect 
the Lord, I won't, sir.

132
00:06:42,535 --> 00:06:44,857
When are you 
coming back for me?

133
00:06:45,515 --> 00:06:48,796
It depends, on how 
well you obey the rules.

134
00:06:48,796 --> 00:06:51,036
Oh, I'll obey, sir. I promise.

135
00:06:59,775 --> 00:07:03,729
So, what did you 
do to this Provo girl?

136
00:07:05,397 --> 00:07:07,551
I lusted for her.

137
00:07:07,551 --> 00:07:09,771
And that got you 
shipped out of town?

138
00:07:09,771 --> 00:07:11,913
It's against our beliefs.

139
00:07:11,913 --> 00:07:13,751
Outside of marriage of course.

140
00:07:13,751 --> 00:07:16,395
So you were pretty 
scared of your dad.

141
00:07:16,952 --> 00:07:19,664
- He was a powerful man.
- He was military.

142
00:07:19,877 --> 00:07:22,211
That's why you 
killed people in uniform.

143
00:07:22,211 --> 00:07:23,922
They reminded you of him?

144
00:07:23,922 --> 00:07:25,055
I loved him.

145
00:07:25,055 --> 00:07:29,158
But you couldn't obey his rules and
that made you lash out.

146
00:07:29,273 --> 00:07:32,088
I followed the rules.

147
00:07:32,088 --> 00:07:35,147
You still get orders?

148
00:07:36,419 --> 00:07:39,305
And the light still shines.

149
00:07:39,305 --> 00:07:40,958
That's why I'm glad I'm getting out.

150
00:07:40,958 --> 00:07:44,329
I have a lot of work to catch up on.

151
00:07:53,521 --> 00:07:55,651
Sure I remember Mike.

152
00:07:55,651 --> 00:07:58,117
He worked the door at the building.

153
00:07:58,117 --> 00:07:59,371
For two years.

154
00:07:59,371 --> 00:08:02,039
We're trying to connect him 
to this guy. Ever seen him?

155
00:08:02,039 --> 00:08:03,976
Sorry. Who is he?

156
00:08:03,976 --> 00:08:05,919
Serial killer. 
Roy Brigham Anthony.

157
00:08:05,919 --> 00:08:07,643
He the guy murdered Mike?

158
00:08:07,643 --> 00:08:10,445
- Could be.
- Oh, that poor kid.

159
00:08:10,445 --> 00:08:13,430
In 30 years, he was probably 
my favorite employee.

160
00:08:13,430 --> 00:08:16,419
- Good guy?
- Charmer. Always had a smile.

161
00:08:16,419 --> 00:08:18,824
And he would go
the extra mile for the tenants.

162
00:08:18,824 --> 00:08:21,362
Do you remember anything 
unusual about the day he died?

163
00:08:21,362 --> 00:08:24,492
- I remember he quit.
- That day?

164
00:08:24,492 --> 00:08:27,169
He gave his notice and 
said he headed to the Big Apple.

165
00:08:27,169 --> 00:08:28,484
To do what?

166
00:08:28,484 --> 00:08:30,148
He had a business idea.

167
00:08:30,148 --> 00:08:33,187
Thought there was 
a future in gourmet coffee.

168
00:08:33,187 --> 00:08:37,250
Which there was. / Kid would've had 
the Starbucks folks beat by a decade.

169
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:39,026
Anyone unhappy about him leaving?

170
00:08:39,026 --> 00:08:42,165
Everyone. Like I said, 
he was a favorite.

171
00:08:42,165 --> 00:08:44,349
But anyone in particular?

172
00:08:44,621 --> 00:08:47,883
Helen Hargrove. 
Her husband owned the building.

173
00:08:47,883 --> 00:08:49,442
She and Mike were close?

174
00:08:49,442 --> 00:08:51,942
Well, you'd see 
those two chatting 24/7,

175
00:08:51,942 --> 00:08:54,252
and he would tell 
her his business plan, etc.

176
00:08:54,252 --> 00:08:56,812
She a big fan of his idea?

177
00:08:56,870 --> 00:08:59,421
Big fan of Mike's.

178
00:09:03,004 --> 00:09:05,193
I'm sorry, Denny, 
I've changed my mind.

179
00:09:05,193 --> 00:09:06,851
I'm not feeling up to going out.

180
00:09:06,851 --> 00:09:08,800
This is Beverly Sill's last tour.

181
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:10,585
I can't make it tonight.

182
00:09:10,585 --> 00:09:13,165
Tonight? 
Don't you mean every night?

183
00:09:13,165 --> 00:09:15,748
I don't know what's wrong. 
Really, I don't.

184
00:09:15,748 --> 00:09:20,256
This is getting tiresome, Helen.

185
00:09:20,415 --> 00:09:22,749
Have a good evening, Mr. Hargrove.

186
00:09:27,853 --> 00:09:30,041
- He's angry.
- I don't blame him.

187
00:09:30,041 --> 00:09:32,032
- Will I see you tonight?
- No.

188
00:09:32,032 --> 00:09:33,404
No? Mike?

189
00:09:33,404 --> 00:09:35,078
We have to stop, Helen.

190
00:09:35,078 --> 00:09:36,536
No, we don't.

191
00:09:36,536 --> 00:09:39,041
You need help. 
Which I can't give you.

192
00:09:39,041 --> 00:09:41,205
You help me every night.

193
00:09:41,205 --> 00:09:44,138
If you don't put 
an end to this, then I will.

194
00:09:44,138 --> 00:09:48,713
- What do you mean by that?
- I'll tell your husband, everything.

195
00:09:48,713 --> 00:09:51,207
- You wouldn't.
- I would.

196
00:10:00,530 --> 00:10:02,110
Some hanky panky?

197
00:10:02,110 --> 00:10:03,567
Well, like I said, she was a fan.

198
00:10:03,567 --> 00:10:06,450
And I did see him in her apartment.

199
00:10:06,450 --> 00:10:10,258
Quite a few times, late night.

200
00:10:10,258 --> 00:10:13,014
Maybe him going the extra mile 
for her got him some trouble?

201
00:10:13,014 --> 00:10:15,443
Mr. Hargrove did have a temper.

202
00:10:15,443 --> 00:10:19,459
And his wife entertaining 
the doorman might have set him off.

203
00:10:19,459 --> 00:10:22,159
No "might" about it.

204
00:10:24,794 --> 00:10:27,408
Looks like Mike Cahill was running 
around with a lady tenant.

205
00:10:27,408 --> 00:10:29,400
Married lady tenant.

206
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:32,510
Kid's caught in a love triangle.
That gives revenge motive to the husband.

207
00:10:32,510 --> 00:10:34,125
Which means 
maybe Roy ain't our guy.

208
00:10:34,125 --> 00:10:36,559
And Jersey's out of luck.

209
00:10:36,641 --> 00:10:41,461
Doorman in Rittenhouse Square 
and a Mormon kid in East falls.

210
00:10:41,461 --> 00:10:44,526
Now how did they meet up 
at the Tasker-Morris stop?

211
00:10:44,526 --> 00:10:47,066
Maybe Roy's aunt 
could shed some light.

212
00:10:47,066 --> 00:10:49,358
One of you's Scotty Valens?

213
00:10:50,772 --> 00:10:54,696
- Who's asking?
- Mark Phillips, NYPD.

214
00:10:56,452 --> 00:10:58,410
Yeah, I'm Valens.

215
00:10:58,410 --> 00:11:00,400
Excuse us, boss.

216
00:11:05,717 --> 00:11:08,189
I understand 
you're Christina's guy.

217
00:11:08,839 --> 00:11:10,734
That's right.

218
00:11:10,734 --> 00:11:12,750
Dating your partner's sister, 
that's gotta be tricky.

219
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:15,649
What do you want, Phillips?

220
00:11:15,906 --> 00:11:19,651
This is a courtesy call. Cop to cop.

221
00:11:19,651 --> 00:11:22,685
I got a warrant for your girl's arrest.

222
00:11:25,213 --> 00:11:26,810
Based on?

223
00:11:26,810 --> 00:11:29,010
I'll talk to her about that.

224
00:11:29,010 --> 00:11:31,558
Yeah, well, whatever it is, it's crap.

225
00:11:31,558 --> 00:11:34,313
Okay. You don't want to get involved,

226
00:11:34,313 --> 00:11:35,846
I'll treat her like a skell.

227
00:11:35,846 --> 00:11:38,579
I'll pick her up tonight and 
haul her ass back to NY.

228
00:11:38,579 --> 00:11:42,378
Or? / Or you could 
arrange a conversation.

229
00:11:42,672 --> 00:11:45,029
This could go easy or hard.

230
